<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN242-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. avaṇai uṟaiyūr ēṇiccēri muṭamōciyār pāṭiyata. ituvumatu – <app><lem wit="#C8">avaṉai yuṟaiyū rēṇiccēri</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3">avaṉaiya<space quantity="8" unit="character"/>rēṇiccēri</rdg></app> muṭamōciyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN241">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>tiṇtē riravalark kītta taṇṭā</l>
<l>raṇṭiraṉ varūu meṉṉa voṇṭoṭi</l>
<l>vaccirat taṭakkai neṭiyōṉ kōyiluṭ</l>
<l>pōrppuṟu muracaṅ kaṟaṅka</l>
<l>vārppeḻun taṉṟāl vicum piṉāṉē.</l></lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>“Antiraṉ with a cool garland, who gave firm chariots </l>
<l>to mendicants, is coming”, so, (1-2c)</l>
<l>while covered drums sounded (4)</l>
<l>in the temple of the Tall one (~ Indra) with the vajra in [his] broad hands with bright bracelets, (2d-3)</l>
<l>rose the roaring to heaven. (5)</l>
            </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
